# Cloudflare Pages _headers
# Security headers for static assets served by the CDN edge (bypasses the Worker).
# NOTE: HSTS and CSP are intentionally omitted here — they are set by middleware.ts
# on SSR responses to avoid duplication. The Worker is authoritative for those headers.

# ── Global headers for all static assets ──────────────────────────────────────
# COOP/COEP are not set here. Legacy `/workspace` was previously isolated for
# SharedArrayBuffer experiments; that route is now redirect-only and the home
# systems strip does not rely on cross-origin isolation for static CDN files.
# If `/` ever needs SAB, add an explicit middleware + CSP review before enabling
# COOP/COEP (and ensure every embedded asset is CORP-safe).
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
